{"title_page": "Bretman Rock", "text_new": "{{Short description|Filipino-American social media personality}}\n'''Bretman Rock''' is a Filipino-American social media personality based in [[Hawaii]]. He started as a comedian and [[meme]] creator on [[YouTube]] and [[Vine (service)|Vine]] before shifting to [[Vlog|vlogs]] and beauty tutorials. \n\n== Career ==\nRock is a Filipino social media personality. He started as a comedian and [[meme]] creator on [[YouTube]] and [[Vine (service)|Vine]] before shifting to [[Vlog|vlogs]] and beauty tutorials.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/asian-beauty-bloggers|title=18 Asian Beauty Bloggers You Need to Follow|last=Corpuz|first=Kristin|date=2018-05-09|website=Teen Vogue|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/style/article/fashion-beauty-fix-online-coronavirus/index.html|title=Where to get your fashion and beauty fix online|last=Cerini|first=Marianna|date=2020-03-18|website=CNN|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> In 2016, one of Rock's [[contouring]] videos went [[Viral video|viral]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elle.com/beauty/makeup-skin-care/a31753822/bretman-rock-look-the-most-do-the-least/|title=Bretman Rock Looks the Most While Doing the Least|last=Walsh|first=Savannah|date=2020-03-19|website=ELLE|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.elitedaily.com/p/bretman-rock-will-star-in-mtvs-no-filter-on-youtube-so-get-ready-19498869|title=OMG, Bretman Rock Is Taking Over MTV's 'No Filter' YouTube Series|last=Kay|first=Mariah|date=2019-12-19|website=Elite Daily|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> He was inspired by [[Talia Joy]] and [[Patrick Starrr]].<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.philstar.com/lifestyle/supreme/2016/03/18/1564284/bretman-rocks|title=Bretman rocks|last=Tatad|first=Gabbie|date=2016-03-18|website=The Philippine Star|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\nHe has earned himself a total of 7.27 million subscribers on YouTube so far and 4 million of the app TikTok.\n\nHe starred as himself in Joey Graceffa\u2019s original YouTube series Escape the Night season 4.\n\nRock did a [[Mukbang|''mukbang'']] with his sister.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/bretman-rock-blonde-nose-piercing|title=Bretman Rock Just Debuted Blonde Hair and a Nose Piercing|last=Russo|first=Gianluca|date=2020-04-26|website=Teen Vogue|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2019, Rock was featured on the [[Pride Month]] cover of the ''[[Gay Times]]''.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cosmo.ph/entertainment/bretman-rock-cover-gay-times-a1031-20190530|title=Bretman Rock Is On The Cover Of \u2018Gay Times!\u2019|last=Esguerra Olarte|first=Steph|date=2019-05-30|website=Cosmo|language=en-ph|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2019, Rock attended his first [[New York Fashion Week]] where he collaborated with stylist Andrew Gelwicks.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.elle.com/beauty/a28984766/bretman-rock-youtube-instagram-interview/|title=Bretman Rock Is the Beauty Influencer You Want to Be Best Friends With|last=Yaptangco|first=Ariana|date=2019-09-13|website=ELLE|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\nOn December 18, 2019, [[MTV]] stated that Rock would be the star of the YouTube show, ''No Filter''.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Personal life ==\nRock, a [[Ilocano people|Ilocano]],<ref name=\":1\" /> was born in the Philippines and moved to [[Hawaii]] at the age of 7.<ref name=\":0\" /> He played sports while growing up including baseball, soccer, cross-country, and volleyball. In high school Rock was on the track team.<ref name=\":1\" /> In November 2019, Rock's father, Edmund Laforga, died after being in a [[coma]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.canadianinquirer.net/2019/11/23/bretman-rock-asks-ph-fans-for-privacy-as-he-mourns-fathers-passing/|title=Bretman Rock asks PH fans for privacy as he mourns father\u2019s passing {{!}} Philippine Canadian Inquirer|last=Deala|first=Joanna Belle|date=2019-11-23|website=Philippine Canadian Inquirer|language=en-CA|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> In September 2019, Rock stated in an interview with [[Elle (magazine)|''Elle'']] that he was in his first relationship.<ref name=\":3\" /> Rock is gay.<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n== Awards and honors ==\nRock was a finalist for the [[Shorty Award|Shorty Award for Breakout YouTuber]] in 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/digital/news/shorty-awards-2017-finalists-1202000652/|title=Shorty Awards 2017 Social-Media Finalists Announced|last=Spangler|first=Todd|date=2017-03-02|website=Variety|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> In 2019, Rock won the Beauty Influencer award at the [[45th People's Choice Awards]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kitv.com/story/41769833/local-beauty-blogger-social-media-influencer-bretman-rock-to-be-a-guest-on-the-ellen-show|title=Local beauty blogger, social media influencer Bretman Rock to be a guest on The Ellen Show|last=|first=|date=2020-02-21|website=KITV|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.khon2.com/local-news/hawaii-local-bretman-rock-nabs-beauty-influencer-of-the-year-title-at-the-peoples-choice-awards-2019/|title=Hawaii local Bretman Rock nabs \u201cBeauty Influencer of the Year\u201d title at the People\u2019s Choice Awards 2019|date=2019-11-11|website=KHON2|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> In 2020, Rock was a finalist in comedy video at the Shorty Awards.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://shortyawards.com/11th/bretman-rock-shrinks-pores-and-takes-the-plunge-with-olehenriksen|title=Bretman Rock Shrinks Pores and Takes The Plunge with OleHenriksen - The Shorty Awards|website=shortyawards.com|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rock, Bretman}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Filipino YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Filipino emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:LGBT YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Male YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Beauty and makeup YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Comedy YouTubers]]\n[[Category:YouTube vloggers]]\n[[Category:American male bloggers]]\n[[Category:American YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Gay entertainers]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from the Philippines]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Hawaii]]\n[[Category:LGBT entertainers from the United States]]\n[[Category:American people of Ilocano descent]]\n[[Category:Hawaii people of Filipino descent]]\n[[Category:LGBT American people of Asian descent]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|Filipino-American social media personality}}\n'''Bretman Rock''' is a Filipino-American social media personality based in [[Hawaii]]. He started as a comedian and [[meme]] creator on [[YouTube]] and [[Vine (service)|Vine]] before shifting to [[Vlog|vlogs]] and beauty tutorials. \n\n== Career ==\nRock is a Filipino social media personality. He started as a comedian and [[meme]] creator on [[YouTube]] and [[Vine (service)|Vine]] before shifting to [[Vlog|vlogs]] and beauty tutorials.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/asian-beauty-bloggers|title=18 Asian Beauty Bloggers You Need to Follow|last=Corpuz|first=Kristin|date=2018-05-09|website=Teen Vogue|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/style/article/fashion-beauty-fix-online-coronavirus/index.html|title=Where to get your fashion and beauty fix online|last=